1
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:16,780
Sharks following the boat brings disaster.

2
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:18,080
According to the rules,

3
00:01:18,080 --> 00:01:20,039
we must throw a body to ward off evil.

4
00:01:20,039 --> 00:01:21,560
Since there is no dead body,

5
00:01:21,560 --> 00:01:23,039
we have to choose one

6
00:01:23,039 --> 00:01:24,000
from you piglets.

7
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,160
You are going to throw a living person

8
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:26,560
into the sea to feed the sharks, right?

9
00:01:26,560 --> 00:01:27,039
Stop.

10
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,240
What year of the Republic is this?

11
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:34,560
You're still doing human sacrifices?

12
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:35,490
What do you know?

13
00:01:36,039 --> 00:01:37,500
This is the will of Heaven.

14
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:40,000
If we don't throw one down to sacrifice to the Dragon King,

15
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,440
the whole ship will die.

16
00:01:42,440 --> 00:01:42,970
Besides,

17
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,120
these piglets

18
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,860
have all signed a bill of sale.

19
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,400
If not them, should we throw you?

20
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:47,759
I...

21
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:48,920
We can't read.

22
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:50,660
So you screw us over like this?

23
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:51,640
Why? Shut up.

24
00:01:52,240 --> 00:01:53,320
Rules are rules.

25
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:55,930
It's clearly written in the contract.

26
00:01:56,440 --> 00:01:57,800
Do you expect the whole ship

27
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:58,680
to die with you?

28
00:01:59,160 --> 00:01:59,960
Wait a minute.

29
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:02,520
You are treating human lives like dirt.

30
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:03,280
We are all Chinese.

31
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:04,240
How can you be so ignorant

32
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:05,880
to harm your own compatriots?

33
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:06,880
Get out of the way.

34
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:07,520
No.

35
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:08,240
If we don't throw them,

36
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,440
will you die for them?

37
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:12,160
Don't get in the way if you don't want to die.

38
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:12,760
Who says it has to be

39
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:13,890
a living sacrifice?

40
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:21,400
To stand up for others,

41
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:22,840
you need to have a solution.

42
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:24,480
A reckless fool like you,

43
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:26,120
who else should we throw?

44
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:27,730
Cut the crap.

45
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:28,760
Where did you come from

46
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:29,760
to cause trouble?

47
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,840
I have a way to avoid casualties

48
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:34,300
and drive away the sharks.

49
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:40,810
Will this

50
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,000
really work?

51
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,460
We won't know until we try.

52
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:55,880
They retreated! They retreated!

53
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:56,840
The sharks really retreated.

54
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,360
Great.

55
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,000
They retreated! They really retreated!

56
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:58,660
Excellent!

57
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,720
The Dragon King has accepted the sacrifice.

58
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:01,320
Great.

59
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:02,720
Finally, some luck.

60
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:04,570
Little girl,

61
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,010
you've got some skills.

62
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,400
You are much better than

63
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:08,800
that useless pretty boy.

64
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:09,560
Break it up.

65
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,240
Break it up.

66
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,040
Disperse.

67
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,440
Thank you.

68
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:17,360
If it weren't for you,

69
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,890
I might have fed the sharks.

70
00:03:19,079 --> 00:03:19,920
You're welcome.

71
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,440
Since I travel by sea often,

72
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:21,920
I naturally know more

73
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:23,050
about these things.

74
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:25,600
It looks to me

75
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:27,780
like it's your first time traveling.

76
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:30,440
I embarrassed myself, Miss.

77
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:35,690
This will calm your nerves.

78
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:38,329
Eating some sweets will make you feel better.

79
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,020
I'm off.

80
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:51,000
This is your first time delivering a living package,

81
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:51,960
and it's a child.

82
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:53,930
Be very careful.

83
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:59,560
My mom used to say when she was alive,

84
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:01,840
if you run into something unhappy,

85
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:03,560
just eat a piece of candy.

86
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:05,560
A sweet taste brings a good mood.

87
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:06,480
Have it.

88
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:17,940
Are you scared?

89
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,079
No, no.

90
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,000
This letter is...

91
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:33,640
This is from an older brother of mine.

92
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:34,900
He sent me this letter.

93
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,720
He is very talented in writing.

94
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:37,840
When I'm bored on the boat,

95
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:39,300
I would take it out to read.

96
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:40,500
It passes the time.

97
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,880
It's a pity that these past few years,

98
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:43,560
I haven't had the chance

99
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:44,960
to visit him in Quanzhou.

100
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:48,280
Wangshu.

101
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:51,720
You are Lin Wangshu?

102
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,760
Wangshu, it's me, Chen Jiadong.

103
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,040
I didn't expect that after 12 years,

104
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:58,040
you'd give me another piece of candy.

105
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:58,800
Jiadong.

106
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:00,370
You're Jiadong.

107
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:00,840
Yes.

108
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:03,560
I haven't seen you in so long.

109
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:09,000
Come, sit down.

110
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,360
Why are you standing?

111
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:12,320
Jiadong.

112
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:13,400
Why are you

113
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,600
on the ship to Malaya?

114
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:16,120
You never mentioned it

115
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,050
in your letters.

116
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,600
Mingshu wrote me a letter saying

117
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,680
he has news about my parents.

118
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,160
I set off as soon as I received the letter.

119
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,880
I didn't expect to meet you here.

120
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:24,760
My brother...

121
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:26,600
he...

122
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,280
went missing.

123
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:30,840
What?

124
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,250
How could he go missing?

125
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:35,080
Half a month ago,

126
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:37,159
he went to the northern suburbs to collect remittances,

127
00:05:37,159 --> 00:05:38,080
and he never

128
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:38,760
came back.

129
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:42,490
How did this happen?

130
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:47,620
Was there anything unusual before he disappeared?

131
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:49,240
Well...

132
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:51,040
Yes.

133
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,800
A few days before he disappeared,

134
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:53,640
I saw him keeping on

135
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:54,560
repeatedly

136
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,600
reading an old newspaper.

137
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,600
An old newspaper?

138
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,120
It was a 12-year-old

139
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:58,780
newspaper.

140
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,960
I think it was about

141
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,800
news of a Japanese tea factory.

142
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:04,560
Right.

143
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:06,640
There also seemed to be a wanted poster.

144
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:08,240
Where is that newspaper now?

145
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,040
Why can they write it,

146
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:10,760
but I can't?

147
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:12,480
No, my friend.

148
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:14,440
Didn't I tell you?

149
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:16,170
These coolie coins of yours

150
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,120
are not currently

151
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,450
circulating currency.

152
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:19,920
You have to wait for the date

153
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:22,760
when the courier collects the remittances to use them.

154
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:23,890
If you're in a hurry,

155
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,200
you can exchange them for cash

156
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:27,440
and come back.

157
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:29,120
Dragon silver, eagle dollars, or Straits dollars,

158
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,120
they're all fine.

159
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,480
But I can't wait!

160
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,400
I don't care.

161
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:33,680
I must send the remittance today.

162
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:34,560
I can't explain it to you.

163
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,680
Who is making trouble

164
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:37,610
in my Wansheng Remittance Bureau?

165
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,050
Wangshu is back.

166
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:41,080
Dad.

167
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,000
Are you okay?

168
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:42,640
I'm fine.

169
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:43,920
I was just explaining to him.

170
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:44,520
How was it?

171
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,560
Did everything go well?

172
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,480
It went smoothly, Dad.

173
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:46,840
Look

174
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:48,080
who I brought back.

175
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:48,720
Are you going to

176
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:49,680
send my letter or not?

177
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:50,000
I...

178
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:51,360
Brother.

179
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:52,400
My dad just

180
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:53,760
explained it very clearly.

181
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:54,760
This is Zhuzai currency,

182
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:55,600
not silver dollars.

183
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:56,920
It can't be mailed separately.

184
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:58,120
You have to wait for the specific day

185
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:59,240
for the courier to collect it

186
00:06:59,240 --> 00:06:59,960
to mail it.

187
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:01,680
If you dare to make trouble again,

188
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:02,760
I won't be polite.

189
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:04,800
Foreigners bully us,

190
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:06,840
and your post office bullies us too.

191
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:08,400
Why won't you let me send my letter?

192
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,160
I really have urgent business.

193
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:09,720
Why can't you

194
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,920
understand plain words?

195
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,520
Wangshu, let me handle this.

196
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,380
Brother, please get up first.

197
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:15,140
Please sit.

198
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:18,690
Brother.

199
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:20,600
What do you want to write?

200
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:22,720
I can help you.

201
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:25,160
I...

202
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,320
My name is Li Laishun.

203
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:38,640
The night before yesterday,

204
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:39,880
I dreamed of my mother

205
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,680
standing by my bed.

206
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,920
She just looked at me without speaking,

207
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,320
and she didn't look too good.

208
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:47,560
Mainly because that day

209
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:50,690
was the day before the anniversary of my mother's death.

210
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:52,880
I've been feeling uneasy.

211
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,250
Dear Xiaocui and Ximei,

212
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,800
The day before yesterday,

213
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:59,159
late at night on June 20th,

214
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,100
I dreamed of my mother.

215
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,040
She stood there silently,

216
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:03,300
with no joy on her face,

217
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,440
which woke me up in fright.

218
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:07,040
I couldn't sleep for the rest of the night,

219
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,370
and felt uneasy all day.

220
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:10,520
The night I had the dream

221
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:13,050
was the eve of my mother's death anniversary.

222
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:15,240
I am sending six silver dollars today.

223
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,880
Four dollars are for household expenses,

224
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:19,960
and two dollars are for the memorial ceremony for my mother.

225
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:20,920
I beg you, sister,

226
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:23,000
to stand before mother's grave and tell her

227
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:25,440
that everything is fine with me in Malaya.

228
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,210
Please don't worry.

229
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:29,000
Your brother, Laishun.

230
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:32,169
Brother Jiadong's writing is indeed excellent.

231
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:33,690
Brother,

232
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:36,480
I've finished writing this Qiaopi for you.

233
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:38,280
But the money...

234
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:41,500
I only have these Zhuzai coins right now.

235
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:43,650
Wangshu,

236
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,200
you tell me what to do.

237
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,600
He wrote the Qiaopi.

238
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,300
He didn't take your money.

239
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:51,560
As for the letter,

240
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:53,160
you now have your own Qiaopi.

241
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:54,560
You just need to wait for the courier

242
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:55,820
to come and collect it,

243
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:57,040
and give him the exchanged silver dollars.

244
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:57,640
That's it.

245
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:00,400
Thank you.

246
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:01,060
Thanks.

247
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,160
It was my fault just now.

248
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:03,090
Thank you, miss,

249
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:03,640
sir,

250
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:04,770
and Boss Lin.

251
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,640
I was just too anxious.

252
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:08,520
All right.

253
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:09,360
We are all Chinese.

254
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,820
I understand how you feel.

255
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:11,640
Thank you.

256
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:12,840
Thank you.

257
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:13,400
Okay.

258
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:14,240
Fine.

259
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,160
Wangshu.

260
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:23,320
Who is this?

261
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:24,400
Dad,

262
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,680
he is Chen Jiadong.

263
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,280
The little boy my brother

264
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:31,000
sent back to Quanzhou 12 years ago.

265
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:31,600
Chen Jiadong.
